definitions.definition: ( humorous , chiefly Greater Boston ) A unit of length defined as exactly sixty-seven inches (approximately 1.70 meters ).

main_definition: ( humorous , chiefly Greater Boston ) A unit of length defined as exactly sixty-seven inches (approximately 1.70 meters ).

definitions.definition: A small opening built into a dry-stone wall, fence, or hedge to allow sheep (and hares) to pass through; a thirl .

main_definition: ( British , dialectal ) A small opening built into a dry-stone wall, fence, or hedge to allow sheep (and hares) to pass through; a thirl .
